vocabulary.definition: a play for theater, radio, or television involving conflict or emotion
vocabulary.example: She starred in a popular drama series on television.

vocabulary.definition: general agreement among a group of people
vocabulary.example: The board reached a consensus on the new policy.

vocabulary.definition: to be disloyal to someone's trust or confidence
vocabulary.example: He felt deeply hurt when he realized he had been betrayed by his friend.

vocabulary.definition: a claim or assertion that someone has done something illegal or wrong
vocabulary.example: The company denied the allegations of misconduct.

vocabulary.definition: not able to be relied on as honest or truthful
